This dataset provides a comprehensive overview of reported crimes across various Indian states and union territories.
It encompasses data spanning multiple years, detailing crime categories such as theft, assault, kidnapping, and cybercrime. 
Each record includes information on the type of crime, location, year, and the number of reported incidents. The dataset is structured to facilitate analysis of 
crime trends,regional disparities, and temporal patterns,making it a valuable resource for researchers, policymakers, and data analysts interested in public safety and criminology in India
